     1	# RELIABILITY.md
     2	
     3	## Purpose
     4	Define the reliability expectations and failure-handling rules for Minakeep.
     5	
     6	## Core Reliability Rules
     7	- every task must name deterministic checks explicitly
     8	- stateful runtime prep must be explicit rather than hidden inside build or test scripts
     9	- operational artifacts under `state/` and `logs/` should be stable and inspectable
    10	- AI enrichment failures must not block note or link persistence
    11	- external AI verification must be explicit instead of assumed from unit tests alone
    12	
    13	## Verification
    14	- `npm run db:prepare` prepares SQLite state and owner seed deterministically
    15	- `npm run start:smoke` boots the production-style server and probes a health endpoint
    16	- `npm run verify` includes startup proof alongside code-level checks
    17	- Ralph status and backlog rendering must work without hand-editing state files
    18	- AI tasks must require a real-endpoint E2E check when `LLM_BASE`, `TOKEN`, and `MODEL` are present
    19	- the real-endpoint Playwright path is tagged `@ai-real`, and promotable AI tasks must pass `npm run test:e2e -- --grep @ai-real` when those env vars are configured
    20	- `npm run verify` does not replace the separate `@ai-real` run for promotable AI work
